entries.femaleVariant: Eyes, they're opening. I think she sees me now.
entries.maleVariant: Eyes, they're opening. I think he sees me now.

entries.femaleVariant: [Try to move] Think so.
[Try to move] Was you I heard?
Think I... can hear...
Heard... voices, lots…
[Sit up] What's that mean?
[Sit up] Sacrificed Johnny – and I'm still damaged goods?
Need to ask... how's So Mi? Everything work out all right?
I've been cut off from updates for a while, now.
Ma'am, your AV is waiting.
V. Can you hear me?
Ugh... 'n' I can talk.
Good. About time.
Was that... you?
Me, doctors, probably some dreams – doesn't matter. You're awake now.
Was told you wouldn't have time for me.
[Lean] So the surgery was a bust?
You're a changed man, Sol.
Was told... you got a new job, new duties, lot's of 'em, busy bear, no time for me.
Reed, uh... 's that you? Seem... different somehow.
Weiss. In the AV. You weren't there.
Ah, right, right... Well, I'm not as busy anymore. 'Sides, I plain wanted to see you.
Stay at Langley long enough, it, uh, makes you its own. I'm no exception.
And the docs said you needed to see a familiar face. Now in particular, so, yeah…
[Lean] Everything all right?
Knew when I'd wake – how?
How'd you know... when I'd wake?
They started bringing you up a few days ago. Controlled process.
Putting in a personal appearance – bad news, gotta be.
Just tell me. Surgery was a bust, right?
Pretty nice welcome. Just missin' flowers and a "Get Well" card.
Given I'm here, guess things worked out all right, huh?
Never that simple. Docs saved you, you're alive…
Hearin' a big-ass "but" in there.
'Cause there is one – deep invasive work on your nervous system, to cut the engram out safely.
[Sit up] Ripper'll fix me.
Could we've done better?
Thank you.
Reed?
This... story –  we do the right thing? Could we have done better?
I don't know, V. And I wont' try answering. Just plain afraid.
Thank you.
Even almost look like… umm…
Who said that? When?
So, how's life, how's things?
Er, paperwork, trainin' recruits – nothin' to write home about.
Not your style of work, sounds like.
I couldn't manage field work anyway, not anymore.
How's things for you?
What ever happened to So Mi?
That it? A good ripper'll patch it quick and easy.
What's that even mean?
Tellin' me I wiped Johnny, sacrificed 'im for nothin'?
Not for nothin' – you're alive.
Not this time.
Your neurons... can no longer handle most implants, chrome.
Your brain can manage your personal link and simple coprocessors... but any use of a combat implant could kill you.
I'm sorry, V, but the life you used to know is gone.
Huh...
There's one other thing.
You were out for two years. It's twenty seventy-nine.
I wish I could help you, V. But I can't.
Fuck.
Gotta be kiddin' me.
You all lied.
I see.
So the future's now.
Fuck. My whole life down the shitter.
It's rough, I know, it'll take getting used to. But it gets better. Trust me.
Two years an' zapped nerves... that all your best docs can manage?
You're shitting me.
Believe me, I wish I could've said it was all good.
Seventy-fuckin'-nine? Ya takin' me for a ride, this some sick joke? Please say it is.
You... fucking hazed me.
Said you'd help me. Instead, you fuckers took it all away.
I see.
That's it? You're takin' it pretty well.
Lackin' the strength to rage at reality. At least – for now.
Huh. Imagined the future'd look a little different.
A joke? Shit, I'm impressed.
What good would it do to rage at reality? Don't see any sense in it.
Night City – when can I go back?
Why didn't the doctors use nanobots?
My implants? What's with them?
Damaged my nervous system... can't believe it. Why didn't they use nanobots?
Neural matrix – apparently it reduced your cells' regenerative capacity.
We tried everything. Really.
What... what about my chrome?
Your implants have been deactivated. It needed doing. Your survival depended on it.
Need to get outta here. NC – when can I go back?
Today, if that's your wish. But you should ask yourself--
Preem. Where's my stuff?
V, listen to me. Your body… it ain't goin' back to what it was.
And NC's a city where you just won't manage. Not anymore.
Please understand. I'd like to spare you that disappointment at least.
Great. And what comes next?
We truly appreciate what you did for us. We can set you up with a job here at Langley.
Know you're tryin' to help.
Don't need your pity.
An' what would I do? Be your assistant, errand rover?
I know you're tryin' to help. And you damn well know that's not for me.
I know I'd feel better seein' you off the street.
Don't need your pity.
Nobody's pitying anybody. We're grateful, so it's a favor to a friend, that's it.
Really don't need your favors…
This isn't my life, Reed.
But it could be, given your old one's long gone.
Not ready for that just yet.
Nah, offers like that – not ready for 'em yet.
Understood. I still wanted you to know right off that you had the option.
Look, my world just shattered, like, into splinters. Really think I can plan my next career move? Besides…
Need to think about it.
Gimme a break.
Dunno, someday, maybe. Need to think. But now, goin' home to NC, definitely.
Up to you.
Reed, please. Just... won't work.
Goin' home, back to NC.
Ehh... sure, your call.
An' if you change your mind, you know where to find me.
Didn't escape death just to waste away here.
Once you know where you're headed, call the nurse.
[Go to window] Need some air.
Keep hearin' the same shit. Why's it nobody can ever help me?
Ugh...! Legs're... jelly. Can barely stand...
Been laid up two years, V.
Need some air.
Me 'n' a Langley gig… Pff.
I know it's not the job of your dreams, but it's a decent prospect.
Nice view out there?
Nice... nice view?
What?
Out the window.
Mhm. Greenery, calm, birds chirping. Not what you're used to.
She's alive, that's all I know.
Same shit, always. Peeps wantin' to help me… never bein' able to, why?
Are you… all right?
I need… I need…
Reed.
Right, that… Wasn't any reason for me to be there then.
Now, yeah, I felt I owed you this.
Our people did everything they could, anything possible.
Doctor's estimates. You were supposed to be conscious by today, tomorrow latest.
Why the hell you care?
No pity here, V. It's an appreciative gesture from the NUSA.
Fuck that kind of gratitude.
Please stop… pretending you care. You don't want me here. Neither of us does.
No need, V. You got no reason to thank me.
[Lean]
[Step away]
[Take]
Or... just admit – I-I-I dunno – that you don't know, aren't sure, whatever…
entries.maleVariant: Or just admit – I dunno, ju--  That you don't know, ya-- You aren't sure, whatever, j--!

entries.femaleVariant: Back on your feet – it's nice to see that, finally.
Ah! First storm this year.
[Look out]
[Step away]
[Touch head]
[Use laptop]
[Use laptop]
